01:00:36,297 --> 01:00:39,901
I will surprise him, and we can
have dinner together,

797
01:00:39,902 --> 01:00:41,871
just the two of us.

798
01:00:42,871 --> 01:00:44,705
Do you like this idea?

799
01:00:44,706 --> 01:00:46,210
Would you help me?

800
01:00:48,210 --> 01:00:50,444
It isn't his birthday.

801
01:00:50,445 --> 01:00:52,846
I know.

802
01:00:52,847 --> 01:00:55,415
I would advise against this,
Alma.

803
01:00:55,416 --> 01:00:56,817
Why?

804
01:00:56,818 --> 01:00:58,252
Because he doesn't like
surprises.

805
01:00:58,253 --> 01:01:00,391
- He does.
- Well, he won't like this one.

806
01:01:02,391 --> 01:01:04,991
I'm trying to surprise him

807
01:01:04,992 --> 01:01:08,331
and love him
the way that I want to.

808
01:01:10,331 --> 01:01:14,201
Well, if you're looking
for something kind to do,

809
01:01:14,202 --> 01:01:17,105
perhaps you could think
of something else.

810
01:01:17,106 --> 01:01:19,339
No, I really must advise
against this, Alma.

811
01:01:19,340 --> 01:01:20,908
I don't think there could be

812
01:01:20,909 --> 01:01:23,810
a more inappropriate time
to try something new.

813
01:01:23,811 --> 01:01:25,812
This is what I want to do,

814
01:01:25,813 --> 01:01:28,485
and I think it will be
very nice.

815
01:01:30,485 --> 01:01:33,356
I respect your advice, Cyril...

816
01:01:34,356 --> 01:01:37,457
but I have to know him
in my own way,

817
01:01:37,458 --> 01:01:40,463
and this is what I want to do
for him.

818
01:01:42,463 --> 01:01:45,031
- Good night.
- Good night.

819
01:01:45,032 --> 01:01:47,834
- Good night, madam.
- Good night, madam.

820
01:01:47,835 --> 01:01:50,378
- Good night, madam.
- Good night.

821
01:01:57,378 --> 01:01:59,853
Good luck.

822
01:02:04,853 --> 01:02:07,501
♪ ♪

823
01:02:19,501 --> 01:02:22,242
(clock ticking quietly)

824
01:02:27,242 --> 01:02:29,514
(opens door)

825
01:02:32,514 --> 01:02:34,186
(closes door)

826
01:02:38,186 --> 01:02:40,154
Oh, Alma.

827
01:02:40,155 --> 01:02:41,922
What is this?

828
01:02:41,923 --> 01:02:44,327
I love you, Reynolds.

829
01:02:46,327 --> 01:02:48,132
Yes, but what is this?

830
01:02:50,132 --> 01:02:52,133
It's a surprise.

831
01:02:52,134 --> 01:02:53,500
Are you hungry?

832
01:02:53,501 --> 01:02:55,937
Where is Cyril?

833
01:02:55,938 --> 01:02:57,404
(Alma clears throat)

834
01:02:57,405 --> 01:02:59,576
I've sent everyone home.

835
01:03:00,576 --> 01:03:03,246
Where is Cyril?

836
01:03:04,246 --> 01:03:05,580
She's left.

837
01:03:05,581 --> 01:03:07,948
What time did she leave?

838
01:03:07,949 --> 01:03:09,353
This afternoon.

839
01:03:12,353 --> 01:03:14,208
I've made us dinner.

840
01:03:33,208 --> 01:03:36,209
Let me collect myself
for a moment.

841
01:03:36,210 --> 01:03:37,278
(clears throat)

842
01:03:37,279 --> 01:03:40,580
I'll just have a bath, I think.

843
01:03:40,581 --> 01:03:43,183
This is very kind of you, Alma.

844
01:03:43,184 --> 01:03:45,620
Would you like a champagne
or a martini?

845
01:03:45,621 --> 01:03:48,488
No, thank you.

846
01:03:48,489 --> 01:03:50,892
Oh, is that your dress?

847
01:03:50,893 --> 01:03:52,292
It's finished.

848
01:03:52,293 --> 01:03:54,503
Let's have a look at it.

849
01:04:01,503 --> 01:04:04,673
Hmm. It's rather interesting.

850
01:04:05,673 --> 01:04:07,942
Very good work.

851
01:04:07,943 --> 01:04:10,377
I'll just have my bath now.

852
01:04:10,378 --> 01:04:12,480
When will Cyril get back?

853
01:04:12,481 --> 01:04:14,389
Mm, tonight?

854
01:04:21,389 --> 01:04:23,548
(approaching footsteps)

855
01:04:47,548 --> 01:04:49,417
(grunts softly)

856
01:04:49,418 --> 01:04:52,092
How was your appointment
with the princess?

857
01:04:57,092 --> 01:05:01,568
She's very beautiful,
like a sculpture of some kind.

858
01:05:06,568 --> 01:05:08,670
Mm-hmm.

859
01:05:09,670 --> 01:05:14,579
(clears throat) So, will you
make her a wedding gown?

860
01:05:17,579 --> 01:05:20,214
I have made her baptism,

861
01:05:20,215 --> 01:05:24,051
her First Communion
and confirmation dresses.

862
01:05:24,052 --> 01:05:26,721
I made the dress
for her presentation at court,

863
01:05:26,722 --> 01:05:30,658
indeed the entire wardrobe
for her coming out season.

864
01:05:30,659 --> 01:05:33,694
It's only right that I should
make her wedding dress,

865
01:05:33,695 --> 01:05:35,562
wouldn't you think?

866
01:05:35,563 --> 01:05:37,064
(softly):
Oh, Christ.

867
01:05:37,065 --> 01:05:41,134
No, but this is not
what I wanted to say.

868
01:05:41,135 --> 01:05:43,738
I'm-I'm sorry, I don't know
what I said, I...

869
01:05:43,739 --> 01:05:46,509
This is meant to be
nice evening.

870
01:05:47,509 --> 01:05:50,663
Let me serve you.

871
01:06:08,663 --> 01:06:11,614
(shaking continues)

872
01:06:26,614 --> 01:06:29,517
Do you like it?

873
01:06:29,518 --> 01:06:31,518
I do.

874
01:06:31,519 --> 01:06:33,821
(continues chewing)

875
01:06:33,822 --> 01:06:36,656
No, you don't.

876
01:06:36,657 --> 01:06:39,392
You don't like it at all.

877
01:06:39,393 --> 01:06:42,529
Usually you always tell me
what you think.

878
01:06:42,530 --> 01:06:44,497
What is this?

879
01:06:44,498 --> 01:06:46,639
You're lying.

880
01:06:51,639 --> 01:06:54,274
As I think you know, Alma,

881
01:06:54,275 --> 01:06:58,114
I prefer my asparagus
with oil and salt.

882
01:06:59,114 --> 01:07:00,613
And knowing this,

883
01:07:00,614 --> 01:07:03,417
you've prepared the asparagus
with butter.

884
01:07:03,418 --> 01:07:06,419
Now, I can imagine
in certain circumstances

885
01:07:06,420 --> 01:07:10,293
being able to pretend
that I like it made this way.

886
01:07:12,293 --> 01:07:15,361
Right now, I'm just admiring
my own gallantry

887
01:07:15,362 --> 01:07:18,835
for eating it the way
you've prepared it.

888
01:07:19,835 --> 01:07:22,806
I don't know
what I'm doing here.

889
01:07:24,806 --> 01:07:27,707
I-I don't know
what I'm doing here.

890
01:07:27,708 --> 01:07:33,449
I'm just waiting around
like an idiot for you.

891
01:07:34,449 --> 01:07:37,250
This was an ambush, Alma.
To what purpose?

892
01:07:37,251 --> 01:07:39,553
This is not...

893
01:07:39,554 --> 01:07:41,589
I know it's not going
as I expected.

894
01:07:41,590 --> 01:07:43,624
I-I didn't mean these things
to come out.

895
01:07:43,625 --> 01:07:46,192
I'm sorry,
but it was meant to be nice.

896
01:07:46,193 --> 01:07:47,595
Well, what did you expect?

897
01:07:47,596 --> 01:07:48,796
I wanted time with you.

898
01:07:48,797 --> 01:07:50,663
I wanted to have you to myself.

899
01:07:50,664 --> 01:07:52,433
You have me all the time.

900
01:07:52,434 --> 01:07:54,201
- No.
- What are you talking about?

901
01:07:54,202 --> 01:07:55,468
I don't.
I... There-there's...

902
01:07:55,469 --> 01:07:57,370
there are always people around.

903
01:07:57,371 --> 01:08:00,140
And if not, then there's
something between us.

904
01:08:00,141 --> 01:08:01,709
- Something between us?
- Yes.

905
01:08:01,710 --> 01:08:03,143
What?

906
01:08:03,144 --> 01:08:05,212
Some...

907
01:08:05,213 --> 01:08:07,750
- What?
- Distance.

908
01:08:08,750 --> 01:08:10,651
When did this happen?

909
01:08:10,652 --> 01:08:13,222
What happened to make you
behave like this?

910
01:08:15,222 --> 01:08:18,895
Is it because you think
I don't need you?

911
01:08:19,895 --> 01:08:22,362
- Yes.
- I don't.

912
01:08:22,363 --> 01:08:24,797
Well, that's very predictable
of you.

913
01:08:24,798 --> 01:08:26,634
Don't act so tough.

914
01:08:26,635 --> 01:08:28,169
I know you are not.

915
01:08:28,170 --> 01:08:29,636
Yeah, that's right.
That's right.

916
01:08:29,637 --> 01:08:30,638
If I don't protect myself,

917
01:08:30,639 --> 01:08:32,907
somebody will come
in the middle of the night

918
01:08:32,908 --> 01:08:34,575
and take over my corner
of the room

919
01:08:34,576 --> 01:08:37,178
and ask me about
their fucking asparagus.

920
01:08:37,179 --> 01:08:38,278
Don't be a bully.
You're being a bully.

921
01:08:38,279 --> 01:08:39,913
There are other things
I'd like to do with my time.

922
01:08:39,914 --> 01:08:41,381
- It's my time. My time!
- I have no idea

923
01:08:41,382 --> 01:08:43,184
what I'm doing here
in your time.

924
01:08:43,185 --> 01:08:44,585
What am I doing here?

925
01:08:44,586 --> 01:08:46,653
I'm standing around like
an idiot waiting for you.

926
01:08:46,654 --> 01:08:48,322
- Waiting for what?
- Waiting for you.

927
01:08:48,323 --> 01:08:50,393
Waiting for what?

928
01:08:51,393 --> 01:08:54,361
Waiting for you
to get rid of me.

929
01:08:54,362 --> 01:08:56,596
To tell me to leave.

930
01:08:56,597 --> 01:08:58,532
So tell me.

931
01:08:58,533 --> 01:09:01,669
So I don't stand around
like a fucking fool.

932
01:09:01,670 --> 01:09:03,670
Asparagus, is this all about
your asparagus?

933
01:09:03,671 --> 01:09:05,706
- No, it's not about asparagus.
- Then what...

934
01:09:05,707 --> 01:09:06,840
the hell is it about?

935
01:09:06,841 --> 01:09:08,408
Are you a special agent
sent here

936
01:09:08,409 --> 01:09:10,376
to ruin my evening
and possibly my entire life?

937
01:09:10,377 --> 01:09:11,879
Why are you so rude to me?

938
01:09:11,880 --> 01:09:13,781
- Why are you talking to me
like this? -Is this my house?

939
01:09:13,782 --> 01:09:15,648
- This is my house, isn't it?
- Yes, this is your house.

940
01:09:15,649 --> 01:09:18,285
- Is this my house?
- Of course it's your house.

941
01:09:18,286 --> 01:09:19,687
Or did somebody drop me
on foreign soil

942
01:09:19,688 --> 01:09:21,589
- behind enemy lines?
- What a question.

943
01:09:21,590 --> 01:09:23,556
- You brought me here.
- I'm surrounded on all sides.

944
01:09:23,557 --> 01:09:24,825
It's you who brought me here.

945
01:09:24,826 --> 01:09:26,559
When the hell did this happen?
Who are you?

946
01:09:26,560 --> 01:09:28,795
Do you have a gun?
You here to kill me?

947
01:09:28,796 --> 01:09:30,898
- Why are you talking like...?
- Hmm? Do you have a gun?

948
01:09:30,899 --> 01:09:33,567
- Stop it! Stop being a child.
- Where's your gun?

949
01:09:33,568 --> 01:09:35,568
- Where's your gun?
- Stop playing.

950
01:09:35,569 --> 01:09:38,438
- Show me your gun.
- Stop playing this game.

951
01:09:38,439 --> 01:09:39,706
- I'm not playing a game.
- I am not.

952
01:09:39,707 --> 01:09:40,941
Yes, mm-hmm, uh-huh.

953
01:09:40,942 --> 01:09:42,643
What game am I playing?
What game?

954
01:09:42,644 --> 01:09:45,278
What precisely is the nature
of my game?

955
01:09:45,279 --> 01:09:46,679
You tell me.

956
01:09:46,680 --> 01:09:47,680
Oh, this whole...

957
01:09:50,018 --> 01:09:51,417
What?

958
01:09:51,418 --> 01:09:52,987
All your rules and your walls

959
01:09:52,988 --> 01:09:55,322
and your doors and your people

960
01:09:55,323 --> 01:09:59,425
and your money and all this
clothes and everything.

961
01:09:59,426 --> 01:10:01,327
This, this, this game!

962
01:10:01,328 --> 01:10:02,595
Everything here!

963
01:10:02,596 --> 01:10:04,497
- The whole... (sputters)
- (silverware clattering)

964
01:10:04,498 --> 01:10:07,734
Nothing is normal
or natural or...

965
01:10:07,735 --> 01:10:09,739
Everything is a game.

966
01:10:11,739 --> 01:10:13,474
"Yes, mister. No, madam.

967
01:10:13,475 --> 01:10:15,509
Yes, uh..." (mutters)

968
01:10:15,510 --> 01:10:17,877
- Well, if it's my...
- "I don't eat this.

969
01:10:17,878 --> 01:10:20,747
- I don't drink that.
I don't do..." -If-if-if...

970
01:10:20,748 --> 01:10:22,383
If it's my life
that you're describing,

971
01:10:22,384 --> 01:10:23,716
it's entirely up to you

972
01:10:23,717 --> 01:10:25,551
whether you choose
to share it or not.

973
01:10:25,552 --> 01:10:27,688
If you don't wish to share
that life, as apparently

974
01:10:27,689 --> 01:10:29,657
it's so disagreeable to you
in every respect,

975
01:10:29,658 --> 01:10:32,693
why don't you just fuck off
to back where you came from?

976
01:10:32,694 --> 01:10:34,064
F... Yeah, mm-hmm.

977
01:10:36,064 --> 01:10:38,302
(departing footsteps)

978
01:10:41,302 --> 01:10:43,648
(door slams shut)

979
01:10:53,648 --> 01:10:55,016
Sometimes, it's good for him

980
01:10:56,016 --> 01:10:59,889
to slow down his steps a little.

981
01:11:00,889 --> 01:11:03,676
(flames crackling)

982
01:11:21,676 --> 01:11:23,137
(birds chirping)

983
01:11:50,137 --> 01:11:52,505
♪ ♪

984
01:12:23,505 --> 01:12:25,948
(talking quietly)

985
01:12:34,948 --> 01:12:38,789
Would you like me to ask Alma
to leave?

986
01:12:41,789 --> 01:12:44,994
No. Why?

987
01:12:46,994 --> 01:12:51,497
Well, if you're going
to make her a ghost...

988
01:12:51,498 --> 01:12:53,032
go ahead and do it,

989
01:12:53,033 --> 01:12:56,005
but, please, don't let her
sit around waiting for you.

990
01:12:57,005 --> 01:12:59,206
I'm very fond of her.

991
01:12:59,207 --> 01:13:01,707
Oh, you're very fond of her,
are you?

992
01:13:01,708 --> 01:13:04,048
- (clears throat)
- Well, in that case...

993
01:13:08,048 --> 01:13:09,750
No, don't turn it on me.

994
01:13:09,751 --> 01:13:11,518
I don't want your cloud
on my head.

995
01:13:11,519 --> 01:13:13,653
- Oh, shut up, Cyril.
- Oh, no, you can shut right up.

996
01:13:13,654 --> 01:13:14,888
Don't pick a fight with me.

997
01:13:14,889 --> 01:13:16,790
You certainly won't
come out alive.

998
01:13:16,791 --> 01:13:18,791
I'll go right through you,
and it'll be you

999
01:13:18,792 --> 01:13:21,222
who ends up on the floor.
Understood?

1000
01:13:48,222 --> 01:13:50,568
♪ ♪

1001
01:14:00,568 --> 01:14:02,983
(Reynolds sighs)

1002
01:14:14,983 --> 01:14:16,860
(clears throat)

1003
01:14:26,860 --> 01:14:28,140
- Morning, Pippa.
- Morning, sir.

1004
01:14:35,103 --> 01:14:36,803
Pen, book and glasses?

1005
01:14:36,804 --> 01:14:38,204
Yes, they're all there
for you, sir.

1006
01:14:39,006 --> 01:14:40,239
Morning, ladies.

1007
01:14:40,240 --> 01:14:42,572
WOMEN:
Good morning, sir.

1008
01:15:10,572 --> 01:15:12,792
(breathy grunt)

1009
01:15:31,792 --> 01:15:34,161
Excellent work, ladies.

1010
01:15:34,162 --> 01:15:36,964
Um...

1011
01:15:36,965 --> 01:15:40,168
(sniffs, sighs)

1012
01:15:41,168 --> 01:15:43,640
It's just not very good, is it?

1013
01:15:45,640 --> 01:15:47,149
It's ugly.

1014
01:15:55,149 --> 01:15:58,085
(women gasping)

1015
01:15:58,086 --> 01:16:00,323
Are you all right, sir?

1016
01:16:02,323 --> 01:16:05,224
(women murmuring)

1017
01:16:05,225 --> 01:16:07,407
(coughing)

1018
01:16:19,407 --> 01:16:21,241
(door closes)

1019
01:16:21,242 --> 01:16:22,408
(water running)

1020
01:16:22,409 --> 01:16:24,314
(door closes in other room)

1021
01:16:27,314 --> 01:16:28,982
Reynolds?

1022
01:16:28,983 --> 01:16:31,953
(Reynolds retching,
water running)

1023
01:16:32,953 --> 01:16:34,787
Reynolds, are you all right?

1024
01:16:34,788 --> 01:16:37,826
(retching continues)

1025
01:16:38,826 --> 01:16:41,728
Mr. Woodcock,
he seems to be ill.

1026
01:16:41,729 --> 01:16:43,897
- Who seems to be ill?
- Mr. Woodcock.

1027
01:16:43,898 --> 01:16:46,002
He's fallen over,
and he's damaged the dress.

1028
01:16:48,002 --> 01:16:50,202
I-I'm sorry, Biddy.
Who's fallen over?

1029
01:16:50,203 --> 01:16:53,172
Mr. Woodcock, he's fallen over,
and he's damaged the dress.

1030
01:16:53,173 --> 01:16:55,142
And there's-there's stains
on the front of the skirt,

1031
01:16:55,143 --> 01:16:57,424
and there's a hole in the bo...
in the lace on the bodice,

1032
01:16:58,011 --> 01:17:00,815
and there's shoe polish
on the front of the dress.

1033
01:17:01,815 --> 01:17:03,351
Shoe polish from what?

1034
01:17:04,351 --> 01:17:05,351
From his shoe.

1035
01:17:07,154 --> 01:17:08,822
I'm fine.
(sniffs)

1036
01:17:08,823 --> 01:17:11,157
Oh, I don't know what the hell
came over me.

1037
01:17:11,158 --> 01:17:13,794
(sniffing, sighs)

1038
01:17:13,795 --> 01:17:15,394
Must be something I've ate.

1039
01:17:15,395 --> 01:17:17,304
Mm-hmm.

1040
01:17:23,304 --> 01:17:25,007
(sighs, moans)

1041
01:17:27,007 --> 01:17:29,242
(moaning)

1042
01:17:29,243 --> 01:17:30,777
You should lie down now.

1043
01:17:30,778 --> 01:17:32,282
No, I'll be fine in a minute.

1044
01:17:34,282 --> 01:17:35,849
Please lie down.

1045
01:17:35,850 --> 01:17:37,718
No, really don't fuss,
Alma, please.

1046
01:17:37,719 --> 01:17:39,152
- I...
- Just don't fuss.

1047
01:17:39,153 --> 01:17:42,322
Whatever it is, if-if you fuss,
I'll die right here.

1048
01:17:42,323 --> 01:17:44,724
(sniffs, sighs)

1049
01:17:44,725 --> 01:17:46,792
I promise I won't fuss.

1050
01:17:46,793 --> 01:17:49,065
(inhales deeply)

1051
