01:38:36,176 --> 01:38:39,411
Didn't I tell you to fuck off?

1304
01:38:39,412 --> 01:38:41,080
Yes. Yes, you did.

1305
01:38:41,081 --> 01:38:43,717
LADY BALTIMORE:
Dinner is served, everybody.

1306
01:38:44,717 --> 01:38:46,287
Come along with me.

1307
01:38:48,287 --> 01:38:51,456
So, that's your
shifty-eyed godson?

1308
01:38:51,457 --> 01:38:53,492
Shifty-eyed?

1309
01:38:53,493 --> 01:38:56,495
He's got perfectly normal eyes.

1310
01:38:56,496 --> 01:38:59,331
I'm rather less fat, I think,
than when you last saw me.

1311
01:38:59,332 --> 01:39:00,300
Really?

1312
01:39:00,301 --> 01:39:02,033
- Yes.
- Thank you very much.

1313
01:39:02,034 --> 01:39:03,669
It's fallen off me.

1314
01:39:03,670 --> 01:39:05,470
Oh, I'm so sorry.

1315
01:39:05,471 --> 01:39:07,272
REYNOLDS:
Very hard to tell sometimes.

1316
01:39:07,273 --> 01:39:10,675
I suppose that, um, there
are secrets nobody tells.

1317
01:39:10,676 --> 01:39:12,144
(Alma laughing)

1318
01:39:12,145 --> 01:39:15,113
Your wife has got
that gorgeous glow

1319
01:39:15,114 --> 01:39:17,116
you get with a first marriage.

1320
01:39:17,117 --> 01:39:19,484
HARDY:
How long will you be here for?

1321
01:39:19,485 --> 01:39:23,625
Seems my godson's rather
enjoying that glow as well.

1322
01:39:25,625 --> 01:39:29,094
So, what are your plans
for New Year's Eve?

1323
01:39:29,095 --> 01:39:32,466
Oh, um... we don't have any.

1324
01:39:34,466 --> 01:39:37,470
Then you should come out
for the Chelsea Arts Club Ball.

1325
01:39:38,470 --> 01:39:39,439
(chuckles)

1326
01:39:39,440 --> 01:39:41,372
- I don't know what that is.
- Well, it's not

1327
01:39:41,373 --> 01:39:42,808
something I'd suggest
if I didn't think

1328
01:39:42,809 --> 01:39:44,242
you'd have a wonderful time.

1329
01:39:44,243 --> 01:39:46,646
It's really something
to be seen.

1330
01:39:47,646 --> 01:39:50,749
(clears throat)
I'll pass it on to my husband,

1331
01:39:50,750 --> 01:39:53,655
but I think we'll stay in.

1332
01:39:56,655 --> 01:39:58,489
Change your mind.

1333
01:39:58,490 --> 01:40:01,160
- Or get him to change his mind.
- (chuckles)

1334
01:40:01,161 --> 01:40:03,062
Or whatever it takes.
Now, please come.

1335
01:40:03,063 --> 01:40:05,568
I promise you
the time of your life.

1336
01:40:08,568 --> 01:40:11,338
How do you know
how my life has been?

1337
01:40:13,338 --> 01:40:15,810
I don't.

1338
01:40:16,810 --> 01:40:18,309
You're right.

1339
01:40:18,310 --> 01:40:20,545
I think this would be
quite a fine time,

1340
01:40:20,546 --> 01:40:23,415
if you'd like to come.

1341
01:40:23,416 --> 01:40:26,689
She's barely looked at you
this evening, has she?

1342
01:40:29,689 --> 01:40:32,462
(loud rattling)

1343
01:40:35,462 --> 01:40:38,429
I think they're well
and truly shaken now.

1344
01:40:38,430 --> 01:40:41,837
(rattling stops;
dice drop on board)

1345
01:40:44,837 --> 01:40:47,108
(muttering quietly)

1346
01:40:48,108 --> 01:40:49,774
What on earth are you doing?

1347
01:40:49,775 --> 01:40:51,210
I rolled a three.

1348
01:40:51,211 --> 01:40:53,211
Yes, but that's the four pip.

1349
01:40:53,212 --> 01:40:55,380
- Get back to the bar
where you belong. -Oh.

1350
01:40:55,381 --> 01:40:57,215
Sorry.

1351
01:40:57,216 --> 01:40:58,649
Let's not start cheating
at this stage, Alma.

1352
01:40:58,650 --> 01:41:00,318
- I'm not cheating.
- (dice rattle on board)

1353
01:41:00,319 --> 01:41:01,853
- I don't need to cheat.
- Oh, good.

1354
01:41:01,854 --> 01:41:04,622
You do need to be able
to count, on the other hand.

1355
01:41:04,623 --> 01:41:07,358
Backgammon, by the way,
I get treble the score

1356
01:41:07,359 --> 01:41:10,429
because you haven't got
any checkers off the board.

1357
01:41:10,430 --> 01:41:11,763
Oh.

1358
01:41:11,764 --> 01:41:12,898
(sputters)

1359
01:41:12,899 --> 01:41:14,366
Stupid game anyway.

1360
01:41:14,367 --> 01:41:15,733
Well, maybe it seems stupid

1361
01:41:15,734 --> 01:41:17,870
to you now,
as you're currently losing,

1362
01:41:17,871 --> 01:41:19,737
but I dare say,
if you were victorious,

1363
01:41:19,738 --> 01:41:22,340
I'm confident you'd see it
in a different light.

1364
01:41:22,341 --> 01:41:24,742
Now, they need your chair
for my next opponent.

1365
01:41:24,743 --> 01:41:26,479
Next.

1366
01:41:27,479 --> 01:41:29,348
- (Reynolds chuckles)
- LADY BALTIMORE: Me, please.

1367
01:41:29,349 --> 01:41:30,681
What?

1368
01:41:30,682 --> 01:41:32,850
What are you so cranky about?

1369
01:41:32,851 --> 01:41:34,486
Have fun with
your next opponent.

1370
01:41:34,487 --> 01:41:37,622
Why, I think I will...
A lot more than I did with you.

1371
01:41:37,623 --> 01:41:39,224
LADY BALTIMORE:
Gosh.

1372
01:41:39,225 --> 01:41:42,229
She's really very rude,
isn't she?

1373
01:41:43,229 --> 01:41:45,264
My heart breaks for you.

1374
01:41:45,265 --> 01:41:47,232
Oh, really?

1375
01:41:47,233 --> 01:41:49,737
Like being married to a toddler.

1376
01:41:50,737 --> 01:41:53,471
I don't want to be racist,
but, I mean...

1377
01:41:53,472 --> 01:41:55,941
is there some sort of custom
at this time of the night

1378
01:41:55,942 --> 01:41:57,475
in her country where...

1379
01:41:57,476 --> 01:41:59,545
- I mean, what is she doing?
- Where what?

1380
01:41:59,546 --> 01:42:02,380
I don't know. I don't know
if she's up stealing things

1381
01:42:02,381 --> 01:42:04,515
or attacking people. I mean...

1382
01:42:04,516 --> 01:42:06,285
MAN (over radio):
we built in civilization.

1383
01:42:06,286 --> 01:42:08,886
I'm all for it when I come
across it, every time...

1384
01:42:08,887 --> 01:42:10,755
I want to go dancing.

1385
01:42:10,756 --> 01:42:14,459
(radio broadcast continues
indistinctly)

1386
01:42:14,460 --> 01:42:16,461
When?

1387
01:42:16,462 --> 01:42:18,201
Right now.

1388
01:42:21,201 --> 01:42:22,968
You're joking.

1389
01:42:22,969 --> 01:42:25,903
No, I'm not.

1390
01:42:25,904 --> 01:42:27,278
It's New Year's Eve.

1391
01:42:32,278 --> 01:42:35,279
Well, I'm not going dancing.

1392
01:42:35,280 --> 01:42:38,684
(pen scratching on paper)

1393
01:42:38,685 --> 01:42:41,286
There's a party
at the Devonshire Hall

1394
01:42:41,287 --> 01:42:43,621
to celebrate the New Year,

1395
01:42:43,622 --> 01:42:46,895
- and I want to go.
- (Reynolds sighs)

1396
01:42:48,895 --> 01:42:51,603
We need to go dancing.

1397
01:42:56,603 --> 01:42:59,237
So, what are you going
to do about it?

1398
01:42:59,238 --> 01:43:01,341
(sighs)

1399
01:43:02,341 --> 01:43:04,776
I'm going to stay right here,

1400
01:43:04,777 --> 01:43:07,480
and I'm going to work.

1401
01:43:08,480 --> 01:43:10,887
(pen scratching on paper)

1402
01:43:15,887 --> 01:43:18,430
(footfalls continue up stairs)

1403
01:43:24,430 --> 01:43:26,609
(footfalls trotting down stairs)

1404
01:43:36,609 --> 01:43:38,878
(door opens)

1405
01:43:39,878 --> 01:43:41,021
(door closes)

1406
01:43:49,021 --> 01:43:51,055
(pen scratching on paper)

1407
01:43:51,056 --> 01:43:53,583
(radio broadcast playing
indistinctly)

1408
01:44:18,583 --> 01:44:20,506
♪ ♪

1409
01:44:40,506 --> 01:44:42,479
(crowd cheering, chattering)

1410
01:44:46,479 --> 01:44:48,824
(band playing festive music)

1411
01:44:58,824 --> 01:45:01,492
MAN (over P.A.): On the hour,
ladies and gentlemen!

1412
01:45:01,493 --> 01:45:03,094
Are you ready to welcome in

1413
01:45:03,095 --> 01:45:05,697
our lovely, glorious,
happy New Year?

1414
01:45:05,698 --> 01:45:06,666
(crowd cheering)

1415
01:45:06,667 --> 01:45:09,100
- Are you ready?
- (crowd shouting, cheering)

1416
01:45:09,101 --> 01:45:10,669
Here we go!

1417
01:45:10,670 --> 01:45:13,404
MAN and CROWD:
Ten, nine, eight,

1418
01:45:13,405 --> 01:45:16,441
seven, six, five,

1419
01:45:16,442 --> 01:45:18,011
four, three, two,

1420
01:45:19,011 --> 01:45:20,144
one!

1421
01:45:20,145 --> 01:45:22,113
Happy New Year!

1422
01:45:22,114 --> 01:45:24,081
(cheering)

1423
01:45:24,082 --> 01:45:27,419
(band playing "Auld Lang Syne")

1424
01:45:27,420 --> 01:45:29,475
(noisemakers blaring)

1425
01:45:49,475 --> 01:45:51,515
(indistinct shouting)

1426
01:45:55,515 --> 01:45:57,497
(Alma gasps)

1427
01:46:12,497 --> 01:46:15,166
(music and crowd noise fade)

1428
01:46:15,167 --> 01:46:17,189
♪ ♪

1429
01:46:37,189 --> 01:46:39,212
♪ ♪

1430
01:46:59,212 --> 01:47:01,667
♪ ♪

1431
01:47:21,667 --> 01:47:23,234
BIDDY:
How does it feel?

1432
01:47:23,235 --> 01:47:26,804
MRS. VAUGHAN: Well, I think
it feels a little big.

1433
01:47:26,805 --> 01:47:28,874
BIDDY: Shall we just
take it in at the waist?

1434
01:47:28,875 --> 01:47:31,242
- We can take it in a little
on the waist. -Yes.

1435
01:47:31,243 --> 01:47:33,144
BIDDY:
Yes, okay, just take it out.

1436
01:47:33,145 --> 01:47:34,850
NANA:
Mm-hmm.

1437
01:47:38,850 --> 01:47:41,086
So, if you can take
a quarter of an inch

1438
01:47:41,087 --> 01:47:42,520
on the double at the waist.

1439
01:47:42,521 --> 01:47:43,988
NANA:
Into nothing but the pin.

1440
01:47:43,989 --> 01:47:45,693
BIDDY:
Yes.

1441
01:47:47,693 --> 01:47:49,260
How's that feeling?

1442
01:47:49,261 --> 01:47:51,095
I think that's better.

1443
01:47:51,096 --> 01:47:54,036
Would you excuse me for
a minute, please, Mrs. Vaughan?

1444
01:47:57,036 --> 01:47:59,270
MRS. VAUGHAN:
Uh, I think it's...

1445
01:47:59,271 --> 01:48:01,939
- BIDDY: How does that feel?
- NANA: Does that feel better?

1446
01:48:01,940 --> 01:48:03,642
BIDDY:
It's not too tight?

1447
01:48:03,643 --> 01:48:05,076
MRS. VAUGHAN:
It's not, no, no.

1448
01:48:05,077 --> 01:48:06,745
- No, it fits fine.
- NANA: It's comfortable?

1449
01:48:06,746 --> 01:48:08,332
BIDDY:
Okay.

1450
01:48:27,332 --> 01:48:29,680
Where has
Henrietta Harding been?

1451
01:48:41,680 --> 01:48:43,113
She's been to another house.

1452
01:48:43,114 --> 01:48:44,992
Which one?

1453
01:48:52,992 --> 01:48:54,358
Why didn't you tell me?

1454
01:48:54,359 --> 01:48:56,801
Because I didn't want to.

1455
01:49:02,801 --> 01:49:04,368
Is there something
I'm unaware of?

1456
01:49:04,369 --> 01:49:06,170
Because,
as far as I can remember,

1457
01:49:06,171 --> 01:49:08,672
all I have done
is to dress her beautifully.

1458
01:49:08,673 --> 01:49:12,176
I don't think that matters
to some people.

1459
01:49:12,177 --> 01:49:15,015
I think they want
what is fashionable and chic.

1460
01:49:16,015 --> 01:49:17,081
Chic?

1461
01:49:17,082 --> 01:49:19,384
Oh, don't you start using
that filthy little word.

1462
01:49:19,385 --> 01:49:20,385
Chic?

1463
01:49:21,020 --> 01:49:22,953
Whoever invented that
ought to be spanked in public.

1464
01:49:22,954 --> 01:49:25,357
I don't... I don't even know
what that word means.

1465
01:49:25,358 --> 01:49:26,992
What is that word?
Fucking chic?

1466
01:49:26,993 --> 01:49:28,993
They should be hung,
drawn and quartered.

1467
01:49:28,994 --> 01:49:29,994
Fucking chic.

1468
01:49:30,029 --> 01:49:32,630
- It shouldn't concern you.
- It does concern me.

1469
01:49:32,631 --> 01:49:33,831
It concerns me very much, Cyril,

1470
01:49:33,832 --> 01:49:35,399
because it's hurt my feelings.

1471
01:49:35,400 --> 01:49:38,845
It's hurt my feelings.

1472
01:49:45,845 --> 01:49:47,649
So, what's all
this moaning about?

1473
01:49:50,649 --> 01:49:52,850
I am not moaning.

1474
01:49:52,851 --> 01:49:55,987
I do not like
to be turned away from.

1475
01:49:55,988 --> 01:49:58,355
Nobody does.

1476
01:49:58,356 --> 01:50:02,212
But I don't want to hear it,
because it hurts my ears.

1477
01:50:20,212 --> 01:50:23,247
I've made a terrible mistake
in my life, Cyril.

1478
01:50:23,248 --> 01:50:25,383
I've made a...

1479
01:50:25,384 --> 01:50:27,786
I've made a terrible mistake.

1480
01:50:27,787 --> 01:50:30,958
I need you to help me.

1481
01:50:33,958 --> 01:50:36,737
What do you want me to do?

1482
01:50:44,737 --> 01:50:46,103
I can't work.

1483
01:50:46,104 --> 01:50:49,773
I can't... concentrate.

1484
01:50:49,774 --> 01:50:51,877
I have no confidence.

1485
01:50:52,877 --> 01:50:55,082
She does not fit in this house.

1486
01:50:57,082 --> 01:51:00,484
We built this house,
the two of us.

1487
01:51:00,485 --> 01:51:02,920
Now she's turning the whole
bloody place upside down.

1488
01:51:02,921 --> 01:51:04,855
She's turning me inside out.

1489
01:51:04,856 --> 01:51:06,925
She's turning you and me
against each other.

1490
01:51:06,926 --> 01:51:12,034
Her arrival has cast
a very long shadow, Cyril.

1491
01:51:16,034 --> 01:51:18,469
Mrs. Vaughan is satisfied
with the dress.

1492
01:51:18,470 --> 01:51:21,072
No one gives a tinker's
fucking curse

1493
01:51:21,073 --> 01:51:24,279
about Mrs. Vaughan's
satisfaction!

1494
01:51:28,279 --> 01:51:30,185
Thank you, Alma.

1495
01:51:33,185 --> 01:51:35,226
Not at all.

1496
01:51:41,226 --> 01:51:44,237
What a model of politeness
you two are.

1497
01:51:51,237 --> 01:51:55,105
There is an air of quiet death
in this house,

1498
01:51:55,106 --> 01:51:58,113
and I do not like
the way it smells.

1499
01:52:02,113 --> 01:52:04,403
♪ ♪

1500
01:52:24,403 --> 01:52:26,088
♪ ♪

1501
01:52:44,088 --> 01:52:46,912
♪ ♪

1502
01:53:06,912 --> 01:53:09,186
♪ ♪

1503
01:53:15,186 --> 01:53:18,922
(water running)

1504
01:53:18,923 --> 01:53:21,600
(water stops running)

1505
01:53:27,600 --> 01:53:29,939
(water running)

1506
01:53:34,939 --> 01:53:36,094
(water stops running)

1507
01:53:55,094 --> 01:53:57,514
(sizzling continues)

1508
01:54:15,514 --> 01:54:17,572
♪ ♪

1509
01:54:40,572 --> 01:54:42,594
♪ ♪

1510
01:55:02,594 --> 01:55:04,708
♪ ♪

1511
01:55:16,708 --> 01:55:19,590
♪ ♪

1512
01:55:31,590 --> 01:55:33,509
(sets pan on counter)

1513
01:55:50,509 --> 01:55:52,542
Would you like a glass of wine?

1514
01:55:52,543 --> 01:55:54,746
No, thank you.

1515
01:55:54,747 --> 01:55:57,215
Can I make you a martini?

1516
01:55:57,216 --> 01:55:59,055
Nothing for me, thanks.

1517
01:56:04,055 --> 01:56:05,422
Water?

1518
01:56:05,423 --> 01:56:07,047
(sighs)

1519
01:56:29,047 --> 01:56:31,601
♪ ♪

1520
01:56:50,601 --> 01:56:53,310
♪ ♪

1521
01:56:58,310 --> 01:57:00,132
(sniffs)

1522
01:57:21,132 --> 01:57:23,175
♪ ♪

1523
01:57:30,175 --> 01:57:32,698
(clears throat quietly)

1524
01:57:52,698 --> 01:57:54,881
♪ ♪

1525
01:58:08,881 --> 01:58:11,266
(chewing continues)

1526
01:58:28,266 --> 01:58:32,475
I want you flat on your back.

1527
01:58:36,475 --> 01:58:38,876
Helpless.

1528
01:58:38,877 --> 01:58:41,514
Tender.

1529
01:58:42,514 --> 01:58:44,817
Open.

1530
01:58:45,817 --> 01:58:48,259
With only me to help.

1531
01:58:54,259 --> 01:58:56,667
And then I want you
strong again.

1532
01:59:02,667 --> 01:59:05,371
You're not going to die.

1533
01:59:06,371 --> 01:59:08,605
You might wish
you were going to die,

1534
01:59:08,606 --> 01:59:10,279
but you're not going to.

1535
01:59:14,279 --> 01:59:17,853
You need to settle down
a little.

1536
01:59:21,853 --> 01:59:24,900
(swallows)

1537
01:59:35,900 --> 01:59:38,568
Kiss me, my girl,
before I'm sick.

1538
01:59:38,569 --> 01:59:40,456
♪ ♪

1539
01:59:57,456 --> 01:59:59,658
(Reynolds groans)

1540
02:00:00,658 --> 02:00:03,861
I think perhaps...
you should telephone

1541
02:00:03,862 --> 02:00:08,002
that boy doctor of yours,
just in case.

1542
02:00:10,002 --> 02:00:12,937
You don't trust me?

1543
02:00:12,938 --> 02:00:15,605
No, I do trust you.
It's just...

1544
02:00:15,606 --> 02:00:17,746
(sighs)

1545
02:00:20,746 --> 02:00:22,813
(Reynolds chuckles softly)

1546
02:00:22,814 --> 02:00:24,016
If you wish.

1547
02:00:25,016 --> 02:00:27,757
But I will make you well again.

1548
02:00:32,757 --> 02:00:34,662
I will.

1549
02:00:36,662 --> 02:00:38,629
I love you.

1550
02:00:38,630 --> 02:00:40,667
I love you, too.

1551
02:00:42,667 --> 02:00:45,036
And I think, perhaps,
you should leave the room.

1552
02:00:45,037 --> 02:00:47,873
(both chuckling)

1553
02:00:48,873 --> 02:00:50,774
Close the door behind you.

1554
02:00:50,775 --> 02:00:52,376
Yes.

1555
02:00:52,377 --> 02:00:54,917
I'll be right outside.

1556
02:00:58,917 --> 02:01:02,519
<i>ALMA: If he didn't wake up
from this...</i>

1557
02:01:02,520 --> 02:01:05,790
<i>if he wasn't here tomorrow...</i>

1558
02:01:05,791 --> 02:01:06,956
<i>no matter.</i>

1559
02:01:06,957 --> 02:01:08,425
Thank you for coming.

